gomodel:SYNGO_1111  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Carroll demonstrates that vesamicol effectively reduces the amount of K+-evoked acetylcholine in brain slices (Table 1). The author isolates crude synaptic vesicle fraction P3 from mouse forebrain, and depolarizes them in high K+ containing buffer in order to deplete the fractions of acetylcholine (Ach). The vesicles are then incubated in solution containing [14C-choline] in the presence or absence of VAchT specific inhibitor vesamicol (also called AH5183). Although 34 nM vesamicol (IC50) reduced the ACh content of the P3 fraction only by 20%, higher concentrations of the inhibitor were shown to inhibit significantly the loading of the P3 vesicles with [14C-choline].. Experimental description: Intriduction:\nTissue fractionation\nThe cytoplasmic (S3) and vesicle-bound (P3) fractions\n(the P3 fraction contains mitochondria, membrane\nfragments and some non-nerve terminal occlusions\nin addition to vesicles) of mouse forebrain were\nprepared according to previously described procedures." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1111" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

